The High Court shall, before sealing a probate or letters of administration under this Act, be satisfied—
(a) that probate duty has been paid in respect of so much, if any, of the estate as is liable to probate duty in Zambia; and
that probate duty has been paid in respect of so much, if any, of the estate as is liable to probate duty in Zambia; and
(b) in the case of letters of administration, that security has been given in a sum sufficient in amount to cover the property, if any, in the territory to which the letters of administration relate;
in the case of letters of administration, that security has been given in a sum sufficient in amount to cover the property, if any, in the territory to which the letters of administration relate;
